VOLATILITY REGIMES (based on ATR z-score):
- LOW (z-score < -1.0): Market too quiet. Insufficient movement, stops too tight. Do NOT trade — output WAIT/SKIP.
- NORMAL (z-score -1.0 to 1.0): Standard conditions. Use 1.0-1.5 ATR stops. Standard position sizing.
- HIGH (z-score 1.0 to 2.0): Elevated volatility. Use wider 1.5-2.0 ATR stops. Position size halved automatically by the system.
- EXTREME (z-score > 2.0): Dangerous conditions. Do NOT trade — output WAIT/SKIP.
